						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in Survey No 104.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagattuṅga—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Jagattuṅga,</hi> refers to the same incident as the one mentioned in the previous inscription, <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> the attack on <hi rend="bold">Pīga</hi> and states that a person whose proper name is not given but who is mentioned only by his title <hi rend="bold">Toṟavaragali</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> a hero among the <hi rend="bold">Toṟavas</hi>) died in that fight, after killing forty-eight (persons).</p>						

						</summary>
